Mr. Waller is a 65-year-old male with a history of rectal cancer who underwent neoadjuvant therapy.  During his preoperative evaluation, he was found to have severe aortic stenosis.  Prior to his colectomy, he underwent an aortic valve replacement which he has recovered from without difficulty. He is now here for surgical resection of his rectosigmoid cancer. Risks, benefits, alternatives, indications, procedure, team approach and advance directives discussed with the patient and he wishes to proceed with surgery.

